In `src/app/api/transfer-transactions/route.ts`, in the GET handler:

1. Inside the `if (search)` block, add a new entry to the `whereClause.OR` array:
   ```typescript
   {
     tags: {
       some: {
         name: {
           contains: search,
           mode: 'insensitive' as Prisma.QueryMode,
         },
       },
     },
   },
   ```

2. After the `accountId` filter block, parse `tagIds` and add it to the where clause. IMPORTANT: The transfer route has special OR handling for `accountId` -- the `tagIds` filter must be added as a separate top-level `tags` property on `whereClause`, NOT inside the OR array. Place it after the accountId block:
   ```typescript
   const tagIds = searchParams.get('tagIds');
   if (tagIds) {
     const tagIdArray = tagIds.split(',').filter(Boolean);
     if (tagIdArray.length > 0) {
       whereClause.tags = {
         some: {
           id: { in: tagIdArray },
         },
       };
     }
   }
   ```
